data.text: Entered into eternal rest on the morning of May 27, 2010, Georgia Wyndham Warder. Residence Charleston, SC. The relatives and friends are invited to attend her funeral service in J. HENRY STUHR, INC., WEST ASHLEY CHAPEL, Saturday, May 29, 2010, at ten o'clock. Interment, Live Oak Memorial Gardens. Friends may call at Stuhr's West Ashley Chapel Friday between five and seven o'clock. Ms. Warder was born April 9, 1928, in Summerville, SC, the daughter of Janie Wyndham Hulett. She was a graduate of St. Andrews High School and a member of the Charleston Women's Bowling Association. She was a member of St. Andrew's Parish United Methodist Church. She retired as Assistant Director of St. Andrews Parks and Playground Department. She is survived by two sons: Ernest C. Warder (Joni) and Robert M. Warder (Andrea); three daughters: Vera W. Mims (Pat), Tina W. Whitehead (Jimmy) and Joanne W. Krider (Dave); 12 grandchildren, 18 great grandchildren and one great-great-grandchild; one brother: Robert Wyndham of Charleston, SC. She is predeceased by Joseph E. Warder and daughter, Bonnie Warder. Memorials may be made to American Heart Association of SC, 409 King Street, Suite 300, Charleston, SC 29403.
